{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8a9d949d-8f0d-4ae5-a9c1-ff5a58458850","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory. I can still guide you on the changes needed to switch from `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` to **NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC)**:\n\n### 1. Add OIDC permissions to your job\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token request\n  contents: read\n```\n\n### 2. Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n    --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n    --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- uses: dotnet/nuget-push@v1\n  with:\n    source: https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nNo API key needed — the action handles OIDC token exchange automatically.\n\n### 3. Register your repo on NuGet.org\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**\n2. Add a **GitHub Actions** publisher, specifying your **repo owner**, **repo name**, and optionally the **workflow filename** and **environment**.\n\n### 4. (Recommended) Use a GitHub Environment\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget-publish   # ties to environment protection rules\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n```\n\nThis scopes the OIDC trust and lets you add approval gates.\n\n### 5. Remove the secret\n\nOnce verified, delete `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repo's **Settings → Secrets**.\n\n---\n\n**Key benefits:** No long-lived secrets to rotate, push authorization is tied to your repo identity, and you can scope trust to specific branches/environments.\n\nWould you like me to help modify a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"718d6865-6311-462b-a74b-89ea1ea8eec5","outputTokens":459,"requestId":"C00D:1BCB52:13763D:172921:69EABEEF"},"id":"ae3107c8-d86a-4f40-b45f-ecd91c2875ea","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:53:15.050Z","parentId":"1e65e8e4-16ca-42e2-b35e-43cec529018a"}
